The Trans Nzoia government will construct two additional modern markets to help enhance business, Governor Patrick Khaemba has said. Speaking in kitale on Monday, Khaemba said his administration has acquired more land from Kitale Prisons and another portion from Kenya Railways on his request. The two markets will make a total of three, as the first one, which is under construction at a cost of Sh200 million is almost complete. "I will soon officially open the first market and business centre, which has been under construction for almost a year," Khaemba said. The governor said his the funds for the new markets will be considered in the 2018-19 financial year.    